.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE LOUBIA-1 V "12 Dec 87" 1988
.RZ "LOUBIA BIL LUZ" "Algerian green beans with almonds"
This is a variation on an Algerian recipe from Rose Dosti's \fIMiddle
Eastern Cooking\fR.  Since when is North Africa in the Middle East? You
may well ask.
.IH "serves 4"
.IG "1 lb" "fresh green beans" "500 g"
.IG "4 cups" "water," "1 liter"
salted
.IG "3 Tbsp" "peanut oil" "50 ml"
.IG "1" "clove garlic,"
mashed
.IG "\(12 tsp" "ground cumin" "2.5 ml"
.IG "\(14 tsp" "paprika" "1 ml"
.IG "\(14 tsp" "ground cloves" "1 ml"
.IG "1 Tbsp" "slivered almonds" "15 g"
.PH
.SK 1
Clean and trim green beans.  Simmer in lightly
salted water until just tender, about
30\-45 minutes.  Drain and put in serving dish.
.SK 2
Put remaining ingredients (except almonds) in a saucepan
over medium heat and cook for two minutes, stirring
constantly.  Add the almonds and stir briefly to coat.
.SK 3
Pour the oil mixture over the green beans and toss gently
until beans are thoroughly coated.  Serve warm.
.NX
Canned green beans are not an acceptable substitute in this recipe. Powdered
garlic is probably OK.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
10 minutes preparation, 50 minutes cooking.
.I Precision:
approximate measurement OK.
.WR
